	(3009,18,'links for 2011-02-21','','http://rex-files.ca/2011/02/links-for-2011-02-21/','69.90.163.60','2011-04-28 00:54:31','2011-04-28 05:54:31','[...] CSS Font-Size: em vs. px vs. pt vs. percent | Kyle Schaeffer &#8230; One of the most confusing aspects of CSS styling is the application of the font-size attribute for text scaling. In CSS, you’re given four different units by which you can measure the size of text as it’s displayed in the web browser. Which of these four units is best suited for the web? It’s a question that’s spawned a diverse variety of debate and criticism. Finding a definitive answer can be difficult, most likely because the question, itself, is so difficult to answer. (tags: font css webdesign development) [...]',0,'1','','pingback',0,0),
