	(3046,18,'Kyle','kylersc@gmail.com','https://kyleschaeffer.com','174.66.14.197','2011-09-07 11:28:01','2011-09-07 16:28:01','Steve, as far as I know, users can always \"zoom,\" regardless of how you set up your fonts. Some users also use a \"text size\" feature in their browser to increase or decrease font sizes as a default setting – this text size feature does not work if you use fixed units like pixels and points.',0,'1','','',3043,1),
