	(3053,18,'Dan','dan@parameterz.com','','66.91.243.20','2011-10-27 01:57:29','2011-10-27 05:57:29','<q cite=\"kyle\"> Pixels are now considered acceptable font size units ... although they are starting to cause some issues as a result of mobile devices with very high density screens</q>\n\nWhich is interesting, given that the <a href=\"http://jquerymobile.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"> JQuery Mobile</a> library/framework makes liberal use of the px-based sizing for their UI, e.g.:\n\n<code>\nlabel.ui-input-text { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; display: block; font-weight: normal; margin: 0 0 .3em; }\n</code>\n\nInteresting and, apparently, timeless post.',0,'1','','',0,0),
