	(3154,18,'Ellie','messagedrom@gmail.com','','37.145.246.169','2015-05-03 09:43:41','2015-05-03 13:43:41','Hello, Kyle, and thanks for the article. It\'s 2015, an still this one is a useful wrap-up. But there\'s one thing that bothers me, and if you find the time to give your opinion on that, I\'d be grateful. I use a similar to yours approach only with rems instead of ems (and a fallback to px). While this is no big problem (plugin does the fallback for me) it means all those extra lines of CSS. So I was wondering -- why not use % throughout all the font-sizes, not only the body. Might seem inconvenient but I suppose once used to it it\'ll be a piece of cake. Are there any disadvantages of using % on all font-sizes?',0,'1','','',0,0),
