	(3226,31,'Jason','jasonwpegg@hotmail.com','','75.165.129.200','2010-04-07 14:34:37','2010-04-07 19:34:37','Great solution!  Since most of my site uses boxes on a white background, I inverted the GIF\'s transparency which allows for any background color to be used in the box.  That way, I\'m changing background color with CSS rather than creating multiple GIF files.  Only works if you\'re against a solid-color background, but that\'s my site.  In any case, thanks!  Love the simplicity of it all!',0,'1','','',0,0),
