	(3344,142,'Kyle','kyle@happylynx.com','http://www.kyleschaeffer.com','64.203.175.98','2010-06-29 09:25:32','2010-06-29 13:25:32','Hi, Aj.  You can use a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> instead of an anchor tag &mdash; The only change will be that you don\'t have to use the <code>display: block;</code> in the CSS.  I add the \"Leaf\" text to the HTML because that\'s what search engines and screen readers will see &mdash; everyone else sees the image, but having more descriptive text makes your design more accessible.',0,'1','','',0,0),
