	(3601,293,'genix','genix@arctoz.de','','92.193.31.57','2009-11-11 15:18:48','2009-11-11 19:18:48','\"[..] increases download times\", why? you can pack the images in one image, and then position the background in the different divs. With that you would have the same download time, but the bubble would be very flexible.',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3602,293,'Kyle','schaeffer.kyle@gmail.com','http://www.kyleschaeffer.com','64.203.175.98','2009-11-12 10:36:35','2009-11-12 14:36:35','Genix, you\'re absolutely right.  I never really thought of it, but I guess you could create a very wide image that would allow you to use a repeating Y-axis background on one side, and have the header/footer image on the other side (which is clipped on the body portion of the chat bubble).  Great idea...I may have to make a new blog post with just that technique.',0,'1','','',0,0),
