	(3618,296,'shanshan','SHANSHANDING@HOTMAIL.COM','','90.94.39.197','2010-06-09 08:37:10','2010-06-09 13:37:10','thanks for the post. But if the background color is not solid and the background is an image. How can we use the rounder corner button?',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3619,296,'Kyle Schaeffer','schaeffer.kyle@gmail.com','http://www.kyleschaeffer.com','65.125.28.253','2010-06-09 11:50:20','2010-06-09 16:50:20','shanshan, if your background is an image (like a gradient color), you\'ll have to take a different approach.  If the size of your box is fixed, you can create a corners image (the same width as the box) for both the top and bottom edges of the box.  I hope this helps!',0,'1','','',0,0),
