	(3726,506,'Gaurav Jain','gaurav_march1987@yahoo.com','','82.204.13.170','2010-08-19 04:04:43','2010-08-19 08:04:43','Can you please tell me what are all possible parameters that we can use:\nI mean like following are the required ones (atleast one of them):\n\'Keywords\',\'Title\',\'Power\',\'BrowseNode\',\'Artist\',\'Author\',\'Actor\',\n\'Director\',\'AudienceRating\',\'Manufacturer\',\'MusicLabel\',\'Composer\',\n\'Publisher\',\'Brand\',\'Conductor\',\'Orchestra\',\'TextStream\',\'Cuisine\',\n\'City\',\'Neighborhood\'.',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3727,506,'Kyle Schaeffer','schaeffer.kyle@gmail.com','http://www.kyleschaeffer.com','204.153.206.2','2010-08-19 11:25:43','2010-08-19 15:25:43','Hi, Guarav. The only params that my PHP method will accept are:\n\n<strong>searchIndex</strong> (required): this is basically the Amazon product \"category\" you\'re searching for; refer to AWS documentation for more info.\n\n<strong>keywords</strong> (required): this is your search terms; pretty self-explanatory\n\n<strong>responseGroup</strong> (optional, default=false): the AWS response group you\'d like to see (default product info., images, related products, etc.); refer to the AWS documentation for a list of all response groups\n\n<strong>operation</strong> (optional, default=itemSearch): this is another configurable param of the AWS web services;  refer to the AWS documentation for more information\n\n<strong>pageNumber</strong> (optional, default=1): the results page you\'d like to have returned\n\nHope this helps!',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3728,506,'Sean','seanhardaker@gmail.com','http://www.seanhardaker.co.uk','62.255.132.102','2010-11-18 18:25:13','2010-11-18 22:25:13','thanks dude, just what i was looking for',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3729,506,'Johannes P Wilbrand','downintheflood@gmail.com','http://www.downintheflood.com','87.123.204.109','2011-01-23 14:19:30','2011-01-23 19:19:30','thanks for your example. did you ever try the new signature requirement with tying in the old xsl stylesheet parameter?',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3730,506,'Kyle','kylersc@gmail.com','https://kyleschaeffer.com','68.229.126.69','2011-01-24 11:39:15','2011-01-24 16:39:15','Hi, Johannes -- nope, never used the XSL stylesheet param, but that\'s a great feature of the web services.  Generally, I transform the XML into HTML via a server-side PHP script, which can in turn use an XSLT file.',0,'1','','',3729,1),
	(3731,506,'Johannes P Wilbrand','downintheflood@gmail.com','http://www.downintheflood.com','87.123.220.26','2011-01-28 12:44:34','2011-01-28 17:44:34','thanks for your reply! i\'m still puzzled as to the requirement of the ContentType &amp; Style parameters, if they must be included in the signed request or should be added later. right now i can\'t seem to get it to work, i got the ItemLookup in general to work though, altering your script at certain places.',0,'1','','',3730,0),
