	(3762,538,'Beru','bearcampi@gmail.com','','125.160.128.83','2011-04-26 02:13:08','2011-04-26 07:13:08','Nice post, but i\'m curious if somebody can explain me how about multiple ajax call in a second, is it stacked or something else.\nCan we replace previous call of ajax with a newer one, because we never know how many second the ajax will be loaded and return, while the new ajax request will be executed soon. As far as i know THERE IS NO WAY TO STOP AN AJAX after it\'s being called.',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(3763,538,'Kyle','kylersc@gmail.com','https://kyleschaeffer.com','174.66.14.197','2011-04-26 08:01:04','2011-04-26 13:01:04','Beru, I think in 99% of cases, you really should try and combine all AJAX requests into a single request.  The idea of stringing multiple AJAX requests together sounds like a bad idea in my opinion.\n\nIf you <em>really</em> want to string them together, you can use the <code>success</code> and <code>error</code> functions to run subsequent requests (these functions aren\'t called until after the initial AJAX request has completed). Simply place a new AJAX request inside one of these functions.',0,'1','','',3762,1),
