	(3776,538,'Carl','carl.scharenberg@gmail.com','http://uncommonguy.com','64.126.93.189','2012-06-29 01:54:31','2012-06-29 05:54:31','This is both elegant and understandable. Easy as an Ajax and JQuery beginner, this code makes sense. I do have a question though. Given this blog post is over 2 years old, is there anything you would change now? Is it still your idea of a \"perfect ajax request\"?',0,'1','','',0,0),
