	(3859,651,'Kyle','kylersc@gmail.com','https://kyleschaeffer.com','174.66.14.197','2012-02-27 10:13:37','2012-02-27 15:13:37','Hi, JO.  Yes, this should work for custom web parts, depending on how they were built.  This script relies on a CSS class called <strong>s4-wpTopTable</strong>.  Most SharePoint 2010 web parts have it, some don\'t, so it entirely depends on how you\'ve set up your web part.',0,'1','','',3858,1),
	(3860,651,'CT','chuething@gmail.com','','202.156.10.9','2012-02-28 08:57:54','2012-02-28 13:57:54','Hi,\n\nI got a strange behavior in Firefox (working in IE and Chrome) although the tab is displayed nicely. The content in the tab is not responding when clicking on asp:TabPanel. Here are the snippet code\n\n[code]\n		  \n                        \n                            \n                                &lt;asp:Label ID=&quot;lblBreakPt&quot; runat=&quot;server&quot; Visible=&quot;false&quot; Text=&quot;\"&gt;\n                            \n                        \n                    \n[/code]',0,'1','','',0,0),
