	(4266,1067,'Aaron','awiley@ambercare.com','','12.185.185.98','2012-10-17 16:44:54','2012-10-17 20:44:54','Hi Kyle, having this issue and here\'s my info: \n(1)Windows 7, IE9 (not seeing in other OS or browsers though haven\'t checked earlier IE\'s) \n(2) SharePoint Foundation 2010 (Bamboo Weather &amp; Fire&amp;Arrow Weather but the latter since uninstalled - have tried this on pages with and without the Bamboo Web Part &amp; problem occurs)\n(3) only small CSS changes to color, addition of breadcrumb trail. \nThank you. Hope this is helpful.',0,'1','','',4172,0),
	(4267,1067,'Shane Perran','shane@graphicalwonder.com','http://www.graphicalwonder.com','142.134.216.62','2012-10-29 18:10:42','2012-10-29 22:10:42','Hi Kyle,\n\nI went through the comments but oddly did not see this issue listed.  If you change the Metatag to render in IE9, versus IE8 compatibility mode which is the default then you cannot move web parts from zone to zone.\n\nEdit page, move web parts, stop editing, the web part goes back to the originaly location.\n\nThis is not the case when in IE8 compatibility mode.\n\nCurious as to if you found a work-around for this?\n\nThanks,\n\nShane',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(4268,1067,'Ali','gouncci@yahoo.ca','','74.114.172.3','2012-11-01 10:33:45','2012-11-01 14:33:45','Hi Kyle,\n\nI would like to add an image banner right above the global navigation on HTML5 Master Page but I don’t know how. Can you please help me out?\n\nThanks a lot in advance,',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(4269,1067,'james','james.mead@worldvision.co.nz','','121.72.170.137','2012-11-03 05:24:05','2012-11-03 09:24:05','Hi I too am having the same issue when selecting \"Add\" on the calendar if i scroll down. Were you able to solve this issue?',0,'1','','',4246,0),
	(4270,1067,'Pepijn Mortimer','pepijn.mortimer@qurius.com','','213.207.112.56','2012-11-05 03:43:10','2012-11-05 08:43:10','I have the same issue. A work-around is to use the Zone Index in the Layouts settings of the web part. The higher the number the lower de web part will be positioned. But with this you are able to place them in any order you\'d like.',0,'1','','',4267,0),
