	(4304,1093,'Brendon','bjwildbore@gmail.com','http://www.bjw.co.nz','130.123.96.22','2012-05-23 18:50:23','2012-05-23 22:50:23','Hi Kyle,\nWhat are your thought on a css-zengarden approach to sharepoint branding? Where the \'zen-garden\' masterpage is never modified but the rebranding is accomplished only with additional css and js files?\nIn your experience, would this be possible.\n\nAlso... love your work!',0,'1','','',0,0),
	(4305,1093,'Anderson','','','210.157.20.86','2013-01-26 01:39:21','2013-01-26 06:39:21','Good points Joern.  Hmm.  In the srpiit of  Don\'t Make Me Think , the user has to think:1. I want to paste text, where do I click? (think-move-click)2. Now I want to click special because that is where the text-only option is, where is that? (think-move-click)3. Now where is that text-only version?  (think-move-click)As opposed to:1. I want to paste text, where do I click? (think-move-click)2. Now where is that text-only version?  (think-move-click)And since the second #2 is so close, you have to think alot less.  It\'s absolutely more optimal and the click is not strong enough to describe it.It\'s less thinking, less moving, less clicking.  Less TMC?',0,'1','','',4301,0),
	(4306,1100,'SharePoint, HTML5, Mobile Web &amp; More | SharePoint 2010 Migration','','http://sharepoint2010.blogs.lincoln.ac.uk/sharepoint-html5-mobile-web-more/','195.195.10.15','2012-03-14 12:50:26','2012-03-14 16:50:26','[...] There are a couple of other useful reads on his site dealing with mobile SharePoint and responsive design here https://kyleschaeffer.com/best-practices/responsive-layouts-using-css-media-queries/ and here https://kyleschaeffer.com/events/html5-css3-mobile-strategy/ [...]',0,'1','','pingback',0,0),
