	(17037,994,'Mark Kuniansky','m_k@bellsouth.net','','159.45.22.8','2016-02-17 13:39:13','2016-02-17 18:39:13','Great list. There is a hint at one of my peeves - fields that move around on the page, depending what you input or select to other fields. Example: Select Unmarried for Marital Status, and a field for Civil Union appears, moving all the rest of the fields down on the page. \r\n\r\nInstead, I\'ve been told to just gray out (not completely hide) the \"not applicable\" fields. Let inputters users at least see the \"hidden\" fields so they know they\'re there but disabled, since that may tip them that they input something wrong. See above example. \r\n\r\nAm I off base here? Fields that move around on the page are a pain in the neck for automated test scripting.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/7.0; rv:11.0) like Gecko','',0,0),
