	(18793,717,'Fernando Silva','setezerocinco@gmail.com','','87.79.92.29','2016-04-28 09:43:52','2016-04-28 13:43:52','Hi. Many thanks for the solution, but I am having the following error when I click on the three dots (...) to open the context menu of a Document: Assertion Failed: Couldn\'t find hard bounding box. Did someone override the \'overflow\' property on the document body? Break into debugger?\r\n\r\nWhen I change the overflow to auto or scroll I have no error, but then I have no horizontal scrolling on mobile. Thanks again for you time and share of knowledge.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/49.0.2623.112 Safari/537.36','',0,0),
	(19197,18,'SammieFox','sammiefox@byom.de','','95.90.221.229','2016-05-04 08:21:19','2016-05-04 12:21:19','Be carefull with this \"62.5%\"-stuff. Its not the same as 10px in Internet Explorer (IE9+) because of their hardware-rendered ClearType®-Specifcation. Its only 9.93px.\r\nhttps://connect.microsoft.com/IE/feedback/details/816709/ie-11-calculating-font-sizes-wrong-when-setting-the-bodys-font-size-in-relative-units\r\n\r\nLets say you have technically a 1168px Layout (defined as 73em) and use 100% font in body, then its really 1168px in all browsers (tested via screenshot). If you use the 62.5% and set the page-width to 116.8em then Internet Explorer is rendering the site with only 1160px (because 9.93px*116.8=~1159.824).  Its like zooming out a little bit. So leave 100% in body to avoid this behaviour if you want identical results in all browsers.',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/50.0.2661.94 Safari/537.36','',0,0),
	(19199,18,'SammieFox','sammiefox@byom.de','','95.90.221.229','2016-05-04 09:00:39','2016-05-04 13:00:39','JSFiddle-Demo: \r\n\r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/j6odgxm6/\r\nFont-Size: 62.5%, Blue bar = 420px, Red bar = 42em\r\nSame length in all browsers, except Internet Explorer \r\n(red bar = 417px instead of 420px, cuz 9.93 * 42 = ~417.06)\r\n\r\nNo problems with 100% font-size: \r\nhttps://jsfiddle.net/72nf3ebq/',0,'1','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/50.0.2661.94 Safari/537.36','',19197,0),
