	(21342,994,'Iris Green','iris.green.b@gmail.com','','193.43.246.250','2016-07-07 08:30:14','2016-07-07 12:30:14','I wonder... what about Web applications? not a web site, but an application which is developed in html? you cannot avoid some of the avoided elements in the list. one example is the pop-up. Not using such popup when user navigates out of a \'dirty\' page (after filling form, or doing other work there), without notification can cost more than the annoyance when all the work is discarded. saving this the data automatically is not always feasible.\r\nso I believe that, even there are gold rules, the secret is to think when to use a solution. and if it\'s annoying - like pop-up, just use it with thought, sparingly, when cost of loosing data is bigger than another click on \'discard\'...',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/51.0.2704.103 Safari/537.36','',0,0),
