	(22452,18,'CSS3的REM设置字体大小 &#8211; NDKBLOG','','http://www.ndkblog.org/2016/09/02/css3%e7%9a%84rem%e8%ae%be%e7%bd%ae%e5%ad%97%e4%bd%93%e5%a4%a7%e5%b0%8f/','114.215.112.203','2016-09-02 04:56:25','2016-09-02 08:56:25','[&#8230;] 在Web中使用什么单位来定义页面的字体大小，至今天为止都还在激烈的争论着，有人说PX做为单位好，有人说EM优点多，还有人在说百分比方便，以至于出现了CSS Font-Size: em vs. px vs. pt vs. percent这样的PK大局。不幸的是，仍然有不同的利弊，使各种技术都不太理想，但又无法不去用。真是进也难，退也难呀。 [&#8230;]',0,'0','The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/4.6','pingback',0,0),
	(22461,31,'Bob','bobstewart581@gmail.com','','173.206.33.249','2016-09-02 21:22:15','2016-09-03 01:22:15','Wow! Extend Studio! I didn\'t know that FlexiCorners costs $40! So much for rounding corners for me. Heck, come on, WYSIWYG lover and code hater, just use border radius!\r\n\r\n    Coders are the behind-the-scenes guy, just at least deal with typing a few lines of code to get a site running in front of your very own eyes! Advertising WYSIWYG software on Kyle\'s coding site is kind of rude, especially for money...\r\n\r\n    Plus, your software is omitting the CSS3 border radius, which makes corners easy to make in a few lines of CSS! Plopping your \"click a button and get instant fancy box\" advertisement on a code blog is not interesting. \r\n\r\n    If not interested, use your own software to make rounded corners on your own site, and advertise it on there. Got that?\r\n\r\n    So, just put your advertisements somewhere else, Extend Studio!\r\n\r\n     included.',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36','',3210,0),
