	(24598,994,'JM','Ptero.4@gmail.com','','190.140.195.145','2016-12-08 15:31:16','2016-12-08 20:31:16','Also\r\n*NEVER HIJACK THE \"VIEW IMAGE\" FUNCTION OF GOOGLE IMAGES (LOOKING AT YOU FANSHARE). If the user wanted to see your f*king website he would have clicked the \"visit website\" button in google images. It\'s infuriating how many websites make it so that when you click the \"view image\" button, either you are redirected to a very low quality version of the image, to a cropped version of the image, a rotated version, a watermarked version, a different image, a fake 404 or 403 page, or to the index page of the website.',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Ubuntu; Linux x86_64; rv:41.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/41.0','',4097,0),
	(24677,994,'Mark Mathews','markmathews66@gmail.com','','120.145.16.73','2016-12-11 01:59:37','2016-12-11 06:59:37','It is amazing how people like different things. You couldn\'t agree more with the search box thing. In this whole article, the only one i disagree with was the search box one. I find nothing more infuriating than having to click on the search box since in early days it was the norm for forms to be used for searching and only search engines used to have them in mass. A quick tip if you do find it annoying. Get very used to the Tab and Shift+Tab combo as if it does annoy you, quite often the simplest and easiest way to get your shortcuts back is one tab push away. I hope they don\'t take away the auto focus on the search box because those sites i absolutely hate it when i can\'t just start typing my search or query. If they took it away, i would either have to click the search box or tab through the links to get to the search box and i would hate nothing more, except for when i click a link and in that short time of clicking, the page has stuffed something on top of what I was clicking and opens a new tab, hence why i found this page. You know, the ones, and the link you attempted to click on is somewhere down the page under this nuisance random content scroll to under the unwanted clickable.',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.0.11700 Safari/537.36','',4121,0),
	(24712,717,'Dani','daniellarmarquez@gmail.com','','152.133.12.69','2016-12-12 12:20:43','2016-12-12 17:20:43','Thanks for this solution! It worked wonders after removing body #s4-ribbonrow position: fixed;',0,'0','Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/54.0.2840.99 Safari/537.36','',0,0),
