	(25794,18,'Paul Crosby | Web Developer &raquo; EMs, REMs, Percentages, Pixels, and Points: Best Practices in Responsive Design','','http://paul-crosby.com/2017/01/12/ems-rems-percentages-pixels-and-points-best-practices-in-responsive-design/','198.71.226.16','2017-01-11 19:20:40','2017-01-12 00:20:40','[&#8230;] Conceptually, percentages are quite similar to ems in that they are relative to the current element. 2em and 200% of 16px are both 32px. There are very subtle differences when using font-size: smallest or font-size: largest. You can find out more about this here. [&#8230;]',0,'0','The Incutio XML-RPC PHP Library -- WordPress/4.7.1','pingback',0,0),
