	(1646,1,'2015-07-13 11:17:29','2015-07-13 15:17:29','This is the second video in a multi-part series in which designer Kyle Schaeffer demonstrates the entire SharePoint user experience design process from beginning to end. In this video, Kyle builds upon the previously completed website wireframes to create fully detailed desktop and mobile design compositions depicting the SharePoint home page.<!--more-->\n\nThis video was published by <a href=\"http://oldrivercreative.com/blog/sharepoint-ux-design-part-two-creative-design\">Old River Creative</a>.\n<div class=\"video-container\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BuVjgqmcf1g\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>','SharePoint UX Design — Part Two: Creative Design','','publish','open','open','','sharepoint-ux-design-part-two-creative-design','','','2015-07-13 11:17:29','2015-07-13 15:17:29','',0,'https://kyleschaeffer.com/?p=1646',0,'post','',1),
	(1809,1,'2015-09-23 12:29:01','2015-09-23 16:29:01','I make websites. It’s what I do. Here, you can find some of my latest projects, designs, and ideas. Mid-Atlantic Athletic Facilities The Project: Design, Creative Ribbon frenzy. http://www.maafmondo.com The Peev The Project: Illustration, Design, Development, SEO This is one of my many creative outlets. Sketches and comics concerning all the things you hate most about life. http://thepeev.com SusQtech The Project: SharePoint 2010, Creative Design, HTML/CSS, jQuery, Master Page, Page Layouts This is an exciting new SharePoint 2010 master page that I designed and created for SusQtech. Construction Management, Inc. The Project: Creative Design With a new public internet site in the making, Construction Management desired a design that evokes a sense of both solidarity and strength. Diagnostic Innovations, LLC The Project: Creative Design, HTML/CSS, jQuery Creative design based around a product-centric website. ThumbSticks The Project: Design, Development, SEO, Marketing This personal project was arguably a little too ambitious, but a good time nonetheless. Medazio The Project: Design, HTML/CSS, SharePoint Medazio is a completely made up word for a completely made up website (used for demonstrating design on the SharePoint 2010 platform). Fresh Air Design Studio Logo The Project: Illustration and Logo Design This new logo was drawn and crafted…','','','publish','closed','closed','','1809','','','2015-09-23 12:54:27','2015-09-23 16:54:27','',0,'https://kyleschaeffer.com/uncategorized/',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),
	(1810,1,'2015-09-23 12:29:01','2015-09-23 16:29:01','Hello, my name is Kyle Schaeffer. For me, it’s all about creativity. I strive to create in all aspects of my life, including my work. Be it web design, graphic design, art, music, writing, or even creative thought, I’m somehow involved in the process of creation at all times. Web design. From the very beginning, interface design came to me as entirely fitting and enjoyable. There is something strangely alluring about the combination of technology and art. They are two things that seem so unfamiliar to each other, so contrasting and dissimilar. Technology is hard, unforgiving, and before all else, logical. Art, on the other hand, is fluid, formless, and ever-changing. It is a timeless beauty that can never truly be defined or generated. Web design, in particular, is a wonderful medium in which the collision of these two seemingly different elements can occur. It combines creative logic as well as visual design, giving designers the opportunity to make something that is both functional and elegant. What it’s all about. While I will always dream for something fantastical and amazing in my life, such as becoming a novelist or perhaps a musician (don’t we all?), the reality of the interim…','','','publish','closed','closed','','1810','','','2015-09-23 12:54:27','2015-09-23 16:54:27','',0,'https://kyleschaeffer.com/uncategorized/',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),
